modules.description: This module implements an HTTP client that establishes connections using a combination of TCP and Happy Eyeballs strategies for efficient address resolution and connection setup. It provides a `connect` function that takes a context and returns an HTTP client handle, supporting asynchronous operations via Lwt. It works with network addresses and TCP sockets, targeting use cases like fast, resilient HTTP requests over IPv4 and IPv6 dual-stack environments.

This module performs HTTP client operations including sending requests and handling responses with support for HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 protocols. It works with data types like `response`, which contains version, status, headers, and body information, and supports TLS configuration, redirects, and custom request headers. Concrete use cases include fetching web resources, interacting with REST APIs, and handling authenticated requests with client certificates.
